Fix use of execute() to get swapname

The output of `execute('swapname')` includes a leading newline character which makes the `swapinfo()` call later on fail. Fixed by trimming the output.

commit.message:
system('uname') might be slow

Shelling out to `uname` and testing whether the operating system is
linux is slow, especially since this is done everytime when vim starts
up. So instead rely on the existence of the /proc directory and assume
it is linux in that case. The existence of that directory was actually
the only reason to test for a linux system in the first place

closes #67

verification.payload:
tree 46ede6d888868be573e76ed49ec05ca0189fbf33
